<subSubSection id="CB9F229EFFF614776B11D4A74E824314" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="833A7115FFF614776B11D4A74E824314" blockId="21.[801,1452,1719,1935]" lastBlockId="22.[136,787,279,559]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">
This species was described from a single collection (
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF614746B7CD4C74C8E47D4" box="[810,999,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Hildebrandt 3329</emphasis>
from Vavatob√© [probably = Ambavatoby, 
<collectingRegion id="4141BFF7FFF614746B77D4E74CC14634" box="[801,936,1783,1807]" country="Madagascar" name="Antsiranana" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Antsiranana</collectingRegion>
]), which has many duplicates; no similar material has been collected since. Though the collected material seems to be well into flower, the sepals and petals are small and often spreading, apparently scarcely accrescent, and the ovary is not strongly conical. In these characters, it resembles the species transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="44850A96FFF51477694CD3074D524014" box="[282,571,279,303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Odontolobus">
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF51477694CD3074EEF4014" box="[282,390,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Homalium</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF5147769E8D3074D524014" box="[446,571,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Odontolobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF514776A6DD3074D564014" box="[571,575,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">.</emphasis>
However, it also has characters more consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="44850A96FFF5147769BAD3274C7A4074" baseAuthorityName="SLEUMER" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[492,787,311,335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Blackwellia" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF5147769BAD3274D354074" box="[492,604,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Homalium</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF514776ACCD3274C7A4074" box="[666,787,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Blackwellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAC2107CFFF5147768DED3474E644054" box="[136,269,343,367]" pageId="22" pageNumber="243" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
; it appears that there is usually only one bract per flower, the calyx tube is cylindrical and well-developed, the upper surface of the ovary is not particularly broad, and the styles are much longer than in most species of 
<taxonomicName id="44850A96FFF514776A24D3A74E6040D4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Homalium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Odontolobus">
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF514776A24D3A74DB640F4" box="[626,735,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Homalium</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF5147768DED3C74E6040D4" box="[136,265,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">Odontolobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B1F1AD07FFF51477695FD3C74E6440D4" box="[265,269,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="243">.</emphasis>
It is suggested that the collected individual was an intersectional hybrid that is not known to persist and does not merit taxonomic recognition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
